        "id": 11059
      },
      "writtenOn": "2021-06-24T19:40:48Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "It looks like you\u0027ve also hardened the API by switching `release` calls into two forms:\n- release() : assert if the expr/stmt is null\n- releaseIfValid() : a null expr/stmt is okay\n\nThis doesn\u0027t seem like a DSL-specific concern. Would it make more sense to just move those checks into each IR node?\n\nSo, release() would go back to its original behavior, the DSL convert calls would go back to just using release(), but at the top of IfStatement::Convert we\u0027d now have this:\n    \n     SkASSERT(ifTrue);\n  \nThis gives us the null checking anywhere that Foo::Convert is called, instead of just here. AFAICS such a check would always be desirable.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 172,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 174,
        "endChar": 0
      },
      "revId": "5f5df36f757eeeed84815bf8744f4b989bc63187",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "c87889fe_dc3f2a78",
        "filename": "src/sksl/dsl/DSLCore.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 5
      },
      "lineNbr": 174,
      "author": {
        "id": 5640
      },
      "writtenOn": "2021-06-25T14:02:08Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Null checks are easy to forget - it seemed best to have \"this can\u0027t be null\" be the default behavior, with the ability to flag the small handful of spots where nulls are actually ok, rather than have to go through the rest of the code and make sure we had appropriate null checks everywhere. Obviously there\u0027s nothing wrong with *also* adding null checks anywhere in SkSL where they\u0027re missing.",
      "parentUuid": "4d52d331_7089d9d7",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 172,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 174,
        "endChar": 0
      },
      "revId": "5f5df36f757eeeed84815bf8744f4b989bc63187",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "c537ef97_ec122322",
        "filename": "src/sksl/dsl/DSLCore.cpp",
